<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the Salmonella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28973452" target="_blank">28973452</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. , and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the Salmonella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24127899" target="_blank">24127899</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the Salmonella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24682814" target="_blank">24682814</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. , and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the Salmonella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimu-rium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22356617" target="_blank">22356617</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E.C. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. , and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the Sal-monella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27206164" target="_blank">27206164</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D. , and Slauch , J. M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the salmonella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27404739" target="_blank">27404739</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chubiz , J.E. , Golubeva , Y.A. , Lin , D. , Miller , L.D , and Slauch , J.M. ( 2010 ) FliZ regulates expression of the sal-monella pathogenicity island 1 invasion locus by controlling HilD protein activity in Salmonella enterica serovar typhimurium .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27341691" target="_blank">27341691</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Moreover , mutants lacking FliZ expression were significantly attenuated in their ability to colonize mouse intestines , but could still cause systemic infection [ 14 , 41 , 51 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21984608" target="_blank">21984608</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is possible that FliZ , EnvZ , and FadD affect hilA expression via HilE , but both published Figure 2 Rationale for interpretation of panels A , B , and C of the bar graphs in Figures 3 -- 6 and Figure S1 , Figure S2 , Figure S3 , Figure S4 , Figure S5 , Figure S6 , Figure S7 , Figure S8 , Figure S9 , Figure S11 , Figure S12 , Figure S13 , Figure S14 , Figure S15 , Figure S16 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22021388" target="_blank">22021388</a>]<br></li>
<li>Saini , S. , Koirala , S. , Floess , E. , Mears , P.J. , Chemla , Y.R. , Golding , I. , et al. ( 2010a ) FliZ induces a kinetic switch in ﬂagellar gene expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21166907" target="_blank">21166907</a>]<br></li>
<li>Most likely , its effect on SPI1 gene expression is through FliZ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20833811" target="_blank">20833811</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note 4 2 that FliZ is indirectly regulated by late protein secretion , as its expression is controlled by 28 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>This indicates that YdiV activates its own expression by inhibiting FliZ expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21804009" target="_blank">21804009</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ boosted fliC expression only when ydiV was concurrently induced ( figure 5B , columns 2 and 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25315056" target="_blank">25315056</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ regulates hilA independently of HilE and RpoS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , we showed that HilE , EnvZ , and FadD regulate SPI1 independently of FliZ .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22021388" target="_blank">22021388</a>]<br></li>
<li>Here , we show that FadD , FliZ , PhoB , and EnvZ/OmpR also require the URS to regulate hilA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11292791" target="_blank">11292791</a>]<br></li>
<li>Finally , epistasis tests showed that PhoB , FadD , FliZ , SirA , and EnvZ act independently to regulate hilA expression and invasion .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10714991" target="_blank">10714991</a>]<br></li>
<li>Previously , we provided evidence that FadD , FliZ , PhoB , SirA , and EnvZ regulate hilA expression by independent pathways ( 48 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11292791" target="_blank">11292791</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ enhances Pclass2 and Pclass3 activity .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>HilE and FliZ act both independently and simultaneously to regulate HilD ( 16 , 20 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29378886" target="_blank">29378886</a>]<br></li>
<li>Through genetic and biochemical analyses , FliZ was found to post-translationally control HilD , and as a result , to positively regulate HilA expression [ 14 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21984608" target="_blank">21984608</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furtherclass2 more , our data suggest that FliZ regulates FlhD4C2 levels posttranslationally .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>It has recently been shown that in E. coli , FliZ negatively regulates RpoS activity posttranslationally , independent of other ﬂagellar proteins ( 37 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our data suggest that FliZ does not directly increase protein translation rates but rather enhances the stability of FlhD4C2 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our results suggest that FliZ regulates the concentration of FlhD4C2 posttranslationally .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , our data suggest that FliZ regulates the FlhD4C2 complex posttranslationally .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>As both FliZ and FliT are activated by the same signal , namely , late protein secretion , an open question is how these two antagonizing regulators operate .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , when the ﬁrst few HBBs are completed and FlgM is secreted at a sufﬁcient rate such that 28 is active , FliZ expression then increases .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>In particular , we imagine that FliZ is dominant at low secretion rates and that FliT is dominant at high secretion rates , for example , in cases when the cell possesses too few or too many active HBBs , respectively .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>As FliZ has a positive effect on Pclass2 activity , one possibility is that it can interact with 70 to activate Pclass2 promoters independent of FlhD4C2 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ activates Pclass2 promoters independent of 28 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results demonstrate that FliZ activation of Pclass2 requires FlhD4C2 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
