<li>It was demonstrated that FliZ posttranslationally controls HilD to positively regulate expression of hilA [ 67 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22632036" target="_blank">22632036</a>]<br></li>
<li>Given that HilD is required for FliZ regulation of hilA , it seemed possible that FliZ could regulate hilD transcription or translation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>]<br></li>
<li>One model that would explain FliZ posttranslational regulation of HilD is that FliZ could negatively regulate HilE expression or function .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>]<br></li>
