<li>They encode an N-terminally hexahistidine-tagged FliZ protein ( His6-FliZ ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21804009" target="_blank">21804009</a>]<br></li>
<li>We asked if FliZ and RcsCDB also function through HilD to control SPI1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17951383" target="_blank">17951383</a>]<br></li>
<li>Through genetic and biochemical analyses , we show that FliZ posttranslationally controls HilD to positively regulate hilA expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>]<br></li>
<li>This indicates that P2 mRNA must contribute to FliZ expression , leading to enhancement of motility development .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21908664" target="_blank">21908664</a>]<br></li>
<li>iV-dependent hysteresis in fliC heterogeneity d f Y el o d o M Metered expression ( figure 5B ) revealed that sensitivity to YdiV and FliZ varies from cell to cell within populations .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25315056" target="_blank">25315056</a>]<br></li>
<li>Another regulator , FliZ , may activate SPI-1 expression by controlling HilD activity ( 13 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24682814" target="_blank">24682814</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , these two indirect effects are assumed to be mediated by FliZ ; RtsB represses FliZ , which has been shown to activate SPI-1 expression but repress type I ﬁmbriae .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>]<br></li>
<li>We demonstrate that FliZ is an FlhD4C2-dependent activator of Pclass2/middle gene-expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>RESULTS FliZ is an activator of Pclass2/middle gene-expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18469103" target="_blank">18469103</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ Is a posttranslational activator of FlhD4C2-dependent flagellar gene-expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25315056" target="_blank">25315056</a>]<br></li>
<li>FliZ is a posttranslational activator of FlhD4C2-dependent ﬂagellar gene-expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19218381" target="_blank">19218381</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20190046" target="_blank">20190046</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20833811" target="_blank">20833811</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29473025" target="_blank">29473025</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21278297" target="_blank">21278297</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23873910" target="_blank">23873910</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20889744" target="_blank">20889744</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25161191" target="_blank">25161191</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21804009" target="_blank">21804009</a>]<br></li>
